OL,3,C'Heartbreaking': Classroom not big
OL,4,Cenough for disabled boy's wheelchair
OL,6,F"There is a piece of paper saying he
OL,7,Fhas access to a certain school but he
OL,8,Fcan't even get up the steps to get in
OL,9,Fthe classroom, so how has he got
OL,10,Faccess?
OL,12,F"There's a little boy here who really
OL,13,Fwants to learn. This is just another
OL,14,Fbarrier for children with
OL,15,Fdisabilities."
OL,17,FMrs Hewer's request for her son to
OL,18,Fstay at nursery until a special school
OL,19,Fplace was available was refused.
